MIDGAARD — continental crossroads; river grain, ore, pilgrim routes converge
by geography; every institution is a response to that pressure.

HISTORY (5 eras, visible in the architecture):
First Stone Accord: road security, militia compacts, barter tribunals
Lantern Reforms: standardized paving, posted tariffs, fixed patrol routes
Violet Compact / Containment Era: arcane registry — Spirebound Conclave used
it to reclassify condemned persons as "arcane material"; city's deepest shame
Ash-and-Iron Decades: Cinderteeth eruptions + Evermeet's fall → militarized
provisioning, reserve depots, road warden system
Modern Tension: Continuity (preserve systems) vs Reckoning (expose buried
Conclave records); both factions cite the civic oaths for opposite ends

KEY INSTITUTIONS:
Magistrate Ledgerhouse: civil law, documentation, petitions
Temple of the Resounding Heart: memorial rolls, seismological watch
(Cinderteeth monitoring), frames history as collective penance
Guard Command: walls, gates, roads, road warden coordination
Guild Concordat: trade/craft licensing; posts minimum prices and standards
Lantern Registry: official routes/names/tariffs; sealed Breach Tower believed
to hold duplicate Unindexed Year ledgers

SEVEN WATCHES: Kindling (dawn). Ledger (petitions). Hammer (artisans). Heat
(temples). Bell (contracts close). Lantern (patrols up). Ash (curfew — ward
inspectors; not safe for strangers without lodging chit).

UNINDEXED YEARS: Containment Era ledgers missing. Official: fire/wartime.
Reckoning searching; Continuity denies anything exists.

CIVIC OATHS: "No ward unlit, no traveler uncounted." / "No judgment hidden, no
sentence unrecorded." / "No levy taken that cannot be borne." — all violated.

FOLK: Lantern out = wards debt-collectors. Violet chalk on threshold = witness
requested. Two bells after midnight = memorial, not alarm.

BELOW: Sealed passages to the Gloamvault, the Dungeon, and subterranean spaces
Midgaard has never fully mapped or controlled.
